  "prompt": "How to add a link in a Quora answer to another Quora answer when using Quora iPhone app?",
  "response": "To add a link to another Quora answer in your Quora answer using the iPhone app, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the Quora App**: Launch the Quora app on your iPhone and navigate to the question where you want to write your answer.\n\n2. **Write Your Answer**: Tap on the \"Answer\" button to start composing your response.\n\n3. **Insert the Link**: You can manually type or paste the link in your answer. To find the link to another answer:\n   - Go to the answer you want to link to.\n   - Tap the share icon (usually represented by an arrow or three dots) and select the option to copy the link.\n   - Return to your answer and paste the link where you want it to appear.\n\n4. **Formatting the Link**: If you want to make the link more readable, you might consider briefly describing the link\u2019s content before or after posting it (e.g., \"For more details on this topic, check out this [answer](link).\"). Note that the Quora app does not support rich text formatting, so you won\u2019t be able to create clickable text directly in the answer.\n\n5. **Submit Your Answer**: Once you've finished writing and adding the link, tap on \"Submit\" to post your answer.\n\nRemember that the link will appear as plain text in the answer, so ensure it\u2019s clear and relevant for readers.",
